.Im MicroEmacs macro;variable
.so me.tni
.TH "@y" 4
.XI "@y" - "Yank buffer variable"
.SH NAME
@y \- Yank buffer variable
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fB@y\fR \- Yank buffer variable
.SH DESCRIPTION
The \fIYank Buffer Variable\fR \fB@y\fR  retrieves the current 
.Ht yank 2
string from the kill buffer and returns it to the caller.
.PP
The \fB@y\fR variable may be set to change the kill ring buffer.
.PP
The \fIYank Buffer  Variable\fR  may be specified with a numeric  qualifier to
access one of the historical yank buffers  \fB@y0\fR to \fB@y15\fR to directly
extract text from the kill-ring.
.SH EXAMPLE
The current  contents of the yank buffer can be obtained using \fB@y\fR, so to
set  variable \fC#l1\fR to the  current or last word if the cursor is not in a
word, simply use:
.Me $emf-scheme
.CS        
    forward-char
    backward-word
    set-mark
    forward-word
    copy-region
    set-variable #l1 @y
.CE 0
.Me $ehf-scheme
